# Art_Style_Guide

## 1. Applies when
Games with a defined visual identity, art direction, and consistent asset pipelines.

## 2. This document owns
Visual art direction and style references.
Color palette, lighting mood, and post-processing targets.
Character, environment, and prop art specifications.
Concept art workflow and iteration process.
Material and shader style guidelines.
UI visual style (in coordination with UI_UX_Design).

## 3. This document does NOT own
Technical art pipeline and tooling (→ Technical_Art).
Animation style and rigging (→ Animation_Design).
UI layout and interaction design (→ UI_UX_Design).
Level layout and composition (→ Level_Design).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Art Direction & Visual Identity · 2. Color Palette & Lighting Mood ·
3. Character Art · 4. Environment & Prop Art · 5. Concept Art Workflow ·
6. Material & Shader Guidelines · 7. UI Visual Style

## 5. Common boundaries
- Art owns "how it looks"; Technical_Art owns "how it's made efficiently".
- Concept art belongs here; production-ready assets belong to asset pipeline docs.
- UI visual style coordinates with but does not replace UI_UX_Design.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Check that character art references Character_Sheets for identity.
- Check that environment art references World_Design for setting.
